#Solar_wind_mission: OMNI (ACE and Wind)
#Solar_wind_mission_source: https://omniweb.gsfc.nasa.gov
#Bow_shock_ID_method: Automated classification of plasma regions using 3D particle energy distributions: https://doi.org/10.1029/2021JA029620
#Rules_of_use: Acknoweldge database by citing paper Lalti et al. 2022 doi:https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2203.04680 (submitted to JGR: space physics)
#Event_type: Terrestrial bow shocks measured by MMS
#Project_website: https://sharp.fmi.fi
#Bow_shock_model_normal: The thickness of the magnetosheath: Constraints on the polytropic index by Farris et al. 1991: https://doi.org/10.1029/91GL02090
#Software_routines: Database generated using open source IRFU MATLAB package: https://github.com/irfu/irfu-matlab
#Units: B [nT] N [cm^-3] V[km/s] T[eV] R [km] Pressure [nPa]
#Co_ordinates: All vectors in the Geocentric Solar Ecliptic System (GSE)
#Time_format: epoch: seconds since the epoch 1 Jan 1970 default used by the ISDAT system.
#Field descriptions:
#direction: Flag indicating if the shock is inbound (1) or outbound (-1)
#time: Date and time interval of the shock crossing in epoch time
#burst_start - burst_end: Burst mode interval [start stop] in epoch time. When burst is unavailable [0 0]
#Bx_us - By_us - Bz_us: Upstream GSE magnetic field vector in nT [x y z]
#B_us_abs: Upstream GSE magnetic field magnitude in nT |B|
#sB_us_abs: standard deviation on the magnitude of the upstream magnetic field
#Delta_theta_B: The maximum rotation of the upstream mangetic field vector in the OMNI interval used
#Ni_us: Upstream ion number density in cubic cm
#Ti_us: Upstream ion temperature in eV
#Vx_us - Vy_us - Vz_us: Upstream GSE solar wind velocity vector [x y z] in km/s
#beta_i_us: Upstream ion plasma beta
#Pdyn_us: Upstream dynamic pressure
#thBn: Shock geometry: Angle between the shock normal and upstream magnetic field in degrees
#sthBn: Standard deviation of thBn based on variation in upstream B in the OMNI interval used
#normal_x - normal_y - normal_z: Shock surface normal (in GSE) according to the model by Farris et al. 1991
#MA: Shock Alfvenic Mach number (assuming shock speed = 0) MA=us_V.normal/us_VA where us_VA is the upstream alfven speed
#sMA: Standard deviation of MA based on variation in upstream B in the OMNI interval used
#Mf: Shock fast mode Mach number (assuming shock speed = 0) Mf=us_V.normal/us_Vf
column2: where us_Vf is the upstream fast mode speed. The electron temperature was taken constant for all shocks at Te = 140000 (k).

column1: #sMf: Standard deviation of Mf based on variation in upstream B in the OMNI interval used
#B_jump: Magnetic field compression ratio
#Ni_jump: Ion density compression ratio
#Te_jump: Electron temperature ratio
#pos_x - pos_y - pos_z: The location of the spacecraft (in GSE and in km) when it observed the shock (MMS1)
#sc_sep_min - sc_sep_max - sc_sep_mean: MMS Spacecraft separation [min max mean] in km
#TQF: Tetrahedron quality factor
#Fill value = -1e30
